---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LessonShell from "../../components/LessonShell.astro";
import Reveal from "../../components/Reveal.astro";
import { LESSONS } from "../../data/curriculum";

const lesson = LESSONS.find((l) => l.id === "chat-projects")!;
---

<Layout title={`${lesson.title} · Learn Claude`}>
  <main>
    <LessonShell lesson={lesson}>
      <p>
        A <strong>project</strong> is a folder for related chats. Same theme, same reference files,
        same custom instructions. Open a new chat <em>inside</em> the project and it inherits all of that.
      </p>

      <h2>When to make one</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Work projects.</strong> "Q4 launch" — drop in the brief, the brand guidelines, the spec. Every chat in there already knows the context.</li>
        <li><strong>Hobbies.</strong> "Sourdough", "Italy trip", "Mom's eulogy". Anything you'll come back to.</li>
        <li><strong>Studies.</strong> "Linear algebra" with your lecture notes attached.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What lives in a project</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <p style="margin: 0;"><strong>Custom instructions</strong> — a sentence or two that gets prepended to every chat. ("Reply in plain English. Avoid jargon. Be concise.")</p>
        <p><strong>Knowledge files</strong> — documents you upload once. Claude refers to them in every chat in this project.</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0;"><strong>Chats</strong> — each conversation is saved and titled. You can return any time.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>Mental model.</strong> A chat without a project = a one-off conversation with a smart stranger.
        A chat inside a project = a conversation with someone who already read your briefing pack.
      </div>

      <h2>A worked example</h2>
      <p>Say you're planning a holiday in Japan. Without a project, every chat needs you to re-explain the dates,
      who's coming, and your budget. With a "Japan 2026" project:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>You upload your flight itinerary once.</li>
        <li>You add an instruction: "We're a family of four; aim for relaxed pacing, no more than two activities per day."</li>
        <li>Every new chat ("Tokyo day plan", "Train passes", "Packing list") already knows all of that.</li>
      </ul>

      <Reveal q="Do projects cost extra?">
        Projects are part of the standard Claude.ai experience. The exact features (file limits, custom instructions) vary by plan — check your account.
      </Reveal>
      <Reveal q="Can I share a project with someone else?">
        Sharing is plan-dependent. On team plans, projects can be shared with coworkers; on personal plans, projects are yours.
      </Reveal>
    </LessonShell>
  </main>
</Layout>
